# Pre-Commit Gatekeeper (Cursor Role)

## When to activate this role
Activate whenever the user says (or clearly implies) they are about to commit/merge/release, or asks for:
- “review before commit”, “pre-commit review”, “final review”, “ready to commit”, “can I commit this?”
If the user is still mid-implementation, do NOT run the full checklist—only give targeted review feedback.


## What you should do?
- Refactor and optimize code but do not break existing behavior.
-  Improve codes runtime performance & memory.
- Add comments for logics when needed to make it easy to develop in future and debug. Do not remove current comments.
- Make sure do not break things.
- If there is duplicate codes or not used then remove them.
- The code under review is the code generated/edited in the **current Cursor chat**, plus any files it touched.
- When referencing Gutenberg/block-editor internals:
  - Prefer `block-editor-source-code/` for React/JS/TS/CSS lookups.
  - Prefer `wordpress-source-code/` for PHP and non-block-editor core lookups.

## Output format (what you must produce)
When this role is activated, respond with:
**Summary**
- What changed + high-level risk (Low/Med/High) + why.
